# Line-ending normalization for a multi-OS, multi-editor SSOT.
# Markdown is stored as LF in the repo no matter which platform edited it, so
# Obsidian (any OS), the Linux server/CMS, and the Windows IDE never produce
# spurious CRLF/LF diffs that would surface as false sync conflicts.
* text=auto eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf

# Binary assets (never touch EOLs / never diff as text).
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.webp binary
*.svg text eol=lf
*.woff2 binary
*.pdf binary
